## Concept and Initial Learning Log Analysis for Lecture Archive Summarization Platform

## Object Recognition from Scientific Document Based on Compartment and Text Blocks Refinement Framework

-   14 December 2023

A new document layout analysis framework called CTBR(Compartment&Text Blocks Refinement) is proposed, which defines scientific documents into hierarchical divisions: base domain, compartment, and text blocks, and utilizes the results of text block classification to implement object recognition within scientific documents based on rule-based compartment segmentation.

## A Low-Jitter Hand Tracking System for Improving Typing Efficiency in Virtual Reality Workspace

](/paper/A-Low-Jitter-Hand-Tracking-System-for-Improving-in-Xu-Gu/465a94621f3815a003b6c0eb0a0adc077065c3ee)

[Tianshu Xu](/author/Tianshu-Xu/2267869732)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[Shinobu Hasegawa](/author/Shinobu-Hasegawa/2267751251)

Computer Science

-   31 October 2023

## Addressing Class Imbalances in Video Time-Series Data for Estimation of Learner Engagement: “Over Sampling with Skipped Moving Average”

](/paper/Addressing-Class-Imbalances-in-Video-Time-Series-of-Zheng-Hasegawa/09cb6777b7acbae4c7b8c8430b70ae9ed832142f)

[Xianwen Zheng](/author/Xianwen-Zheng/1818117480)[Shinobu Hasegawa](/author/Shinobu-Hasegawa/2267751251)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)

Computer Science, Education

-   22 May 2024

This research introduces “Skipped Moving Average”, an innovative oversampling technique designed to augment video time-series data representing disengaged students and demonstrates that the proposed method outperforms others in terms of both performance and stability across sequence deep learning models.
